column4: "Work on initiatives set by and with the USUSA President. Its function/form is different from year-to-year."

"Advisory board to the University President and chaired by the USUSA Executive VP. Decides on student fees. Receives presentations, discusses, reviews, & votes on whether or not to recommend a change in student fees. Applications usually open up towards the end of September."

"Advocate for student interests to their college's administration (deans & department heads), plan & execute service projects & college specific events. Each college has its own week filled with events."
"Create lifelong aggies. Focuses on donors and guest speakers. Engage alumni. Plan & execute initiatives to connect students with alumni. Also, True Aggie Night, Miss USU, and A-Day."

"The National Society of Collegiate Scholars (NSCS) is an honors organization that recognizes and elevates high-achieving students. NSCS provides career and graduate school connections, leadership, and service opportunities, and gives out more than $1 million annually in scholarships, awards, and chapter funds."
"Entomology Club helps educate the community about the spectacular and important world of insects through educational outreach events."

"USUSA ASPIRE will allow students to students to get involved with the National Science Foundation-funded ASPIRE Engineering Research Center. This club will allow students to get involved with ASPIRE's goal to reimagine and innovate the transportation system as we know it. At the Campus level, students will participate firsthand in research and innovation with the opportunity to serve on the international student organization."
